Class ClientConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object

      • getExecutor

        public Executor getExecutor()
        Returns the executor which must be used by the client to process requests. If there is an executor configured for the client, some processing will happen in the executor, instead of the caller thread. The methods executed asynchronously will depend on the client and its configuration (i.e. sync / async stub, BIO/NIO...).
        Returns:
        the executor the client must use to process requests.

      • isSteamingEnabled

        public boolean isSteamingEnabled()
        Configures the client stack to advertise or not streaming capability.
        Returns:
        if true streaming capability will be advertised in the accept HTTP header.
